When this prayer is completed the priest and the deacon say also the Cherubimic hymn, thrice, the priest with his hands raised up, and the deacon holding his orarion up high with three fingers of his right 
hand, and each time, at the conclusion thereof, they bow once.
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Priest:}{
 Let us, who mystically represent the Cherubim and chant the thrice-holy hymn unto the life-creating Trinity, now lay aside all earthly cares: \line \~\line }{\b\i Deacon:}{ That we may receive the King of 
all, Who cometh invisibly upborne in triumph by the ranks of angels. Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
The deacon, taking the censer and placing incense therein, approacheth the priest, (in current practice, he censeth while the priest is saying the secret pr
ayer, or the priest, if he serve alone, censeth immediately after the secret prayer) and taking a blessing from him, censeth round about the whole table, and the whole altar, and the whole altar and the priest, and he sayeth the 50th Psalm and the tropari
a of compunction, and whatsoever he may wish, together with the priest. \line }{\fs32 \~\line }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest goeth to the table of oblation, the deacon preceding, and the deacon or priest censeth the holy things, praying secretly: 

\par }{\b\i\fs36\cf15 Deacon:}{\f1\fs36\cf15  O God cleanse me, a sinner. }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Thrice \line }{\fs32 \~\line }{\b\i\fs36\cf15 Deacon:}{\f1\fs36\cf15  Lift up, Master.}{\fs36  
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest taking the aer and layeth it upon the deacon's left shoulder saying:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Priest:}{ Lift up your hands to the holies, and bless the Lord.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
Then taking the holy diskos, he placeth it upon the deacon's head, with all attent
iveness and reverence, the deacon also having the censer in one of his fingers. The priest himself, taketh the holy chalice in his hands and they come out by the North door, the candle-bearers going before them, and they make the circuit of the temple whi
le praying:
\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs36\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h28}{\*\bkmkend h28}The Great Entrance
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
The Orthodox episcopate of the Russian Church; our lord the Very Most Reverend N., Metropolitan of Eastern America and New York, the First Hierarch of the Russian Church Abroad; and our lord the Most Reverend Bishop N.
, may the Lord God remember in His kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
After chanting his petition, the deacon immediately enters the sanctuary through the holy doors and kneels on his right knee only, holding the diskos on the right corner of the holy table. The priest intoneth the following petitions during the entrance.

\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
The much suffering Russian Land and its Orthodox people both in the homeland and in the diaspora; this land, its authorities and the faithful that dwell therein, may the Lord God remember in His kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. 

\par The clergy, the monastics, all that are persecuted and suffer for the Orthodox Faith; the founders, benefactors, and the brotherhood of this holy temple ( or 
holy monastery), and all of you Orthodox Christians, may the Lord God remember in His kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages}{\cs47\b\i\fs36 . 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain 
\s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest passeth through the holy doors. And the people say: 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 People: May the Lord God remember thy prie
sthood in His Kingdom, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 As the priest passeth through the holy doors the deacon says to him:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\ql \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Deacon:}{ May the Lord God remember thy priesthood in His kingdom. \line 
\~}{\b\i Priest:}{ May the Lord God remember thy sacred diaconate in His kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages.
\par }{\cs44\i\fs28\cf6 And the priest then placeth the holy chalice on the Holy Table and taking the holy diskos from the head of the deacon, and placeth it on the Holy Table saying:}{\fs32 
\par }{\b\i Priest: }{The noble Joseph, having taken Thy most pure Body down from the Tree and wrapped it in pure linen and covered It with spices, laid It in a new tomb. \line }{\fs32 \~\line }{
In the grave bodily, but in Hades with Thy soul as God; in Paradise with the thief, and on the throne with the Father and
 the Spirit wast Thou Who fillest all things, O Christ the Inexpressible. How life-giving, how much more beautiful than Paradise and truly more resplendent than any royal palace hath Thy tomb appeared, O Christ, the source of our resurrection. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Then taking
 the veils from the holy diskos and the holy chalice, he layeth them to one side of the altar (in current practice, each is unfolded, and placed on the right and left side of the holy table, over the red cloth and under the cross on each side.) And taking
 the aer from the deacon's shoulder, and having censed it, he covereth the Holy Gifts therewith, saying:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Priest:}{
 The noble Joseph, having taken Thy most pure Body down from the Tree and wrapped It in pure linen and covered It with spices, laid It in a new tomb. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And taking the censer from the hand of the deacon, he censeth the Holy Gifts thrice, saying:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Priest:}{
 Do good, O Lord, in Thy good pleasure unto Sion, and let the walls of Jerusalem be builded. Then shalt Thou be pleased with a sacrifice of righteousness, with oblation and whole-burnt offerings. Then shall they offer bullocks upon Thine altar.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The holy doors and curtain are closed.
\par \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And having returned the censer, and having lowered his phelonion, and having bowed his head, he saith to the Deacon: 
\par }{\b\i\fs32\cf15 Priest:}{\f1\fs32\cf15  Remember me, brother and concelebrant. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the deacon saith to him: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Deacon:}{ May the Lord God remember thy priesthood in His Kingdom. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
Then the deacon, bowing his head, holding his orarion with three fingers of his right hand, says to the Priest:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Deacon:}{ Pray for me, holy Master. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the }{\cs44\b\i\f1\fs20\cf6 Priest:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Priest:}{
 The Holy Spirit shall come upon thee, and the power of the Most High shall overshadow thee. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the Deacon: }{\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\ql \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Deacon:}{
 The same Spirit shall minister with us all the days of our life. \line \~}{\b\i Deacon:}{ Remember me, holy Master. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the Priest: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\ql \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Priest:}{
 May the Lord God remember thee in his kingdom, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. \line \~}{\b\i Deacon:}{ Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And having kissed the right hand of the priest, he goeth out the North door, and standing in the usual place, saith:
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof 
