\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 That we may be delivered from all tribulation wrath, and necessity, let us pray to the Lord. 
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\fs20 People: Lord, have mercy. }{\fs32 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Help us, save us, have mercy on us, and keep us, O God, by Thy grace. 
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\fs20 People: Lord, have mercy. }{\fs32 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 That the whole day may be perfect, holy, peaceful, and sinless, let us ask of the Lord. 
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\fs20 People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 An angel of peace, a faithful guide, a guardian of our souls and bodies, let us ask of the Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\fs20 People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Pardon and remission of our sins and offenses, let us ask the Lord. 
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\fs20 People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Things good and profitable for our souls and bodies, and peace for the world, let us ask of the Lord. 
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\fs20 People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 That we may complete the remaining time of our life in peace and repentance let us ask of the Lord.  
\par }\pard \qj \fi720\li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20 People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 A Christian en
ding to our life, painless, blameless, peaceful; and a good defense before the dread Judgment Seat of Christ, let us ask. \tab \tab \tab \tab   }{\fs20 People: Grant this, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Calling to remembrance our most holy, most pure, most blessed, glorious Lady Theotokos and 
ever-virgin Mary, with all the Saints, let us commit ourselves and each other, and all our life unto Christ our God.    }{\fs20 People: To thee, O Lord.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
The deacon moves to stand before the icon of Christ while priest finisheth the prayer of Proskomedia.
\par }\pard\plain \qc \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 {\*\bkmkstart h30}{\*\bkmkend h30}The Prayer of the Proskomedia}{\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i Priest:}{
 O Lord God Almighty, who alone art holy, Who dost accept a sacrifice of praise from them that call upon Thee with their whole heart: Accept also the supplication of us sinners, and bring it to Thy Holy Altar, and enable us to 
offer unto Thee both gifts and spiritual sacrifices for our sins and for the errors of the people, and vouchsafe us to find grace before Thee, that our sacrifice may be acceptable unto Thee, and that the good Spirit of Thy grace may rest upon us, and upon
 these Gifts set forth, and upon all Thy people.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Exclamation:
