\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And the priest, breaking it into four parts with attentiveness and reverence, saith:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 Broken and distributed is the Lamb of God, broken, yet not divided; ever eaten, though never consumed, but sanctifying them that partake thereof.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The deacon, pointing to the holy chalice with his orarion saith:}{\fs32  
