\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
The priest, taking the portion which lieth at the top, that is IC, maketh a cross over the holy chalice therewith, saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ The fullness of the Holy Spirit. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 and thus he placeth it in the holy chalice.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And taking the warm water, he saith to the Priest: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Bless the warm water, Master. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The priest blesseth it, saying:}{\fs32  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  Blessed is the fervor of Thy saints, always, now and ever, and unto the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the deacon poureth cruciformly into the holy chalice whatever is sufficient, saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ The fervor of faith, full of the Holy Spirit. Amen.

\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And having set aside the warm water, he standeth near
 the high place, facing the holy table with his arms folded crosswise. 
\par Concerning the Breaking of the Holy Lamb. \line \~\line It is necessary for thee to know, O priest, that on breaking the Holy Lamb thou must place the part with the sign of the Cross downward on 
the holy diskos, the incised side upward, as before when it was cut. IC, therefore, is placed at the upper side of the holy diskos, which is toward the east. And XC, at the bottom, which is toward the west; and that which is NI, upon the North side; and K
A, on the South side.
\par }\pard \s25\qj \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
Taking the portion IC, therefore, place it into the holy chalice. And divide the portion XC among the priests and deacons. Divide the other two portions, namely NI and KA, among the communicants in small particles, as many as may be su
fficient according to thine own estimation. But of the portion of the most holy Theotokos, or of the nine orders of saints, or any others which are upon the holy diskos, thou shalt in no wise communicate anyone; only of the two portions which remain of th
e Holy Lamb shalt thou give in Communion. \line \~\line 
Furthermore, be it known unto Thee also concerning this: that when thou dost dilute with the holy hot water the Divine Blood of the Master, then thou shalt pour with discretion so that there be enough for all tha
t desire to partake. So also the wine and water, when thou dost pierce the Holy Lamb, thou art to pour at that time an amount sufficient for all; after this, thou shalt pour no more, but only that which is necessary for the dilution at: Holy Things are fo
r the Holy, and thus communicate all therefrom. 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs36\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h40}{\*\bkmkend h40}The Communion of the Clergy
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the priest and deacon bow thrice as the priest sayeth: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\ql \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ O God, cleanse me a sinner. }{\cs44\i\fs28\cf6 Thrice.
}{ \line \~O God, absolve, remit and pardon our voluntary and involuntary sins, in word and deed, known and unknown, by day and night, in mind and thought; forgive us all, in thy goodness and love for men. 
\par Deacon, Draw nigh. \line \~}{\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{ Behold, I approach unto the immortal King and our God. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And approaching, the deacon maketh a bow, reveren
tly asking forgiveness. The priest, holding the Holy Bread, giveth it to the deacon; and the deacon having kissed the hand of him that giveth, receiveth the Holy Bread saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Deacon:}{
 Impart unto me, Master the precious and holy Body of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ To the sacred Deacon }{\cs44\i\cf6 N.}{ is imparted the precious, and holy, and most pure Body of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ, unto the remission of his sins, and life everlasting. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And, bowing his head, the deacon goeth behin
d the holy table and prayeth as doth the priest saying 'I believe, O Lord', and the rest. 
\par \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain \s25\qj \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl 
\pard\plain \s25\qj \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Likewise the priest, taking one portion of the Holy Bread, saith: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 Behold, I approach unto Christ, the immortal King and our God. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ The precious and most holy Body of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ is imparted unto me, the Priest }{\cs44\i\cf6 N.,}{ unto the remission of my sins, and life everlasting. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And bowing his head, he prayeth, saying:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 I believe, O Lord, and I confess that Thou art truly the
 Christ, the Son of the living God, who didst come into the world to save sinners, of whom I am chief. Moreover, I believe that this is truly Thy most pure Body, and that this is truly Thine own precious Blood. Wherefore, I pray Thee: Have mercy on me and
 forgive me my transgressions, voluntary and involuntary, whether in word or deed, in knowledge or in ignorance. And vouchsafe me to partake without condemnation of Thy most pure Mysteries unto the remission of sins and life everlasting. Amen. \line \~
\line Of thy Mystical Supper, O Son of God, receive me today as a communicant; for I will not speak of the Mystery to Thine enemies, nor will I give Thee a kiss as did Judas, but like the Thief do I confess Thee: Remember me, O Lord in Thy kingdom. \line 
\~
\par Let not the communion of Thy Holy Mysteries be unto me for judgment or condemnation, O Lord, but for healing of soul and body. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain 
\s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And thus they partake of that which they hold in their hands with fear and all heedfulness. Then rising, the priest taketh the chalice in both hands with the cloth and partaketh thrice from it saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 Of the precious and holy Blood of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ do I, the servant of God, the priest N., partake unto the remission of my sins and life everlasting. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And thus, 
having wiped his lips and the holy chalice with the cloth which he holdeth in his hand, he saith:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 Behold, this hath touched my lips, and taketh away mine iniquities, and purgeth away my sins. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Then he calleth the deacon, saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{ Deacon, draw nigh. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And the deacon approacheth, and boweth down once, saying:
\par Impart unto me, Master, the precious and holy Blood of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ. 
\par And the priest saith:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 The servant of God, the Deacon N., partaketh of the precious and holy Blood of our Lord and God and Savior Jesus Christ unto the remission of his sins and life everlasting. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The deacon having partaken, the priest saith:
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 Behold, this hath touched thy lips, and taketh away thine iniquities, and purgeth away thy sins.
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
It should be known, that if there be those who wish to partake of the Holy Mysteries, the priest breaketh the two portions of the Holy Lamb that remain, that is, NI and KA, into small pieces, so that there be sufficient for all communicants, and 
then putteth them in the holy cup. \line }{\fs32 \~\line }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And he covereth the holy chalice with its veil, likewise also on the holy diskos he placeth the star and its veil. 
\par }{\fs32 \~\line }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And he saith the prayer:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s45\qj \li576\ri576\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin576\lin576\itap0 \f1\fs36\cf15\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\fs28 Priest:}{
 We give thanks unto Thee, O Master, lover of mankind, benefactor o
f our souls, that on this very day Thou hast vouchsafed unto us thy heavenly and immortal Mysteries. Direct our way, establish us all in Thy fear, preserve our life, make steadfast our steps, through the intercession and supplications of the glorious Theo
tokos and Ever-Virgin Mary and of all Thy saints. 
\par }\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs36\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs40 {\*\bkmkstart h41}{\*\bkmkend h41}\sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl 
\pard\plain \s19\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs36\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs40 The Communion of the Faithful
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And then they open the doors of the holy altar. And the deacon, bowing once, receiveth the holy chalice with reverence, and approacheth the doors, and elevating the holy chalice, showeth it to the people, saying: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Deacon:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 With fear of God, and with faith and love, draw nigh. 
\par }\pard \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\fs20 People: Blessed is he that cometh in the Name of the Lord; God is the Lord and hath appeared unto us. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 The Priest saith the prayer 'I believe, O Lord and 
I confess ...' and the rest (as he said himself before communing) with the people. Then those that desire to partake draw nigh. And they come one by one, and bow down with compunction and fear, having their arms folded on their breasts. Then each one rece
iveth the Divine Mysteries. The priest, as he communicateth each one saith:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  The servant (handmaid) of God }{\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6 N.}{\fs32 
 partaketh of the precious and holy Body and Blood of our Lord God and Savior Jesus Christ, unto the remission of sins and unto life everlasting. Behold, this hath touched thy lips, and taketh away thine iniquities, and purgeth away thy sins. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\qj \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 
And the deacon wipeth the communicant's lips with the cloth, and the communicant kisseth the holy cup, and bowing, withdraweth. And in this manner do all partake. Meanwhile the following hymn is repeated until all have communicated:
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 People: Receive ye the Body of Christ; taste ye the Fountain of Immortality}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 And after the last hast communicated:
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li720\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20 People: Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 After communion, the 
priest entereth the holy altar and placeth the Holy Things on the Holy Table. The deacon then holdeth the holy diskos over the holy chalice, while emptying the remaining Holy Bread into the chalice, saying these Resurrection Hymns: 
