Rich men have turned poor and gone hungry; but they that seek the Lord shall not be deprived of any good thing. \line Come ye children, hearken unto me; I will teach you the fear of the Lord. \line 
What man is there that desireth life, who loveth to see good days? \line Keep thy tongue from evil, and thy lips from speaking guile. \line Turn away from evil, and do good; seek peace, and pursue it. \line 
The eyes of the Lord are upon the righteous, and His ears are opened unto their supplication. \line The face of the Lord is against them that do evil, utterly to destroy the remembrance of them from the earth. \line 
