\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Reader: }{\fs32 I thank Thee, O Lord my God, that Thou hast not rejected me, a sinner, but hast vouchsafed me to be a communicant of Thy holy Things. I thank Thee that Thou hast vouchsafed me, the unworthy, to partake of
 Thy most pure and heavenly Gifts. But, O Lord, Lover of mankind, Who for our sake didst die and rise again and didst bestow upon us these Thy dread and life-giving Mysteries for the well-being and sanctification of our souls and bodies, grant that these 
m
ay be even unto me for the healing of both soul and body, for the averting of everything hostile, for the enlightenment of the eyes of my heart, for the peace of the powers of my soul, for faith unashamed, for love unfeigned, for the fullness of wisdom, f
o
r the keeping of Thy commandments, for an increase of Thy divine grace, and for the attainment of Thy Kingdom; that being preserved by Them in Thy holiness I may ever remember Thy grace, and no longer live for myself but for Thee our Master and Benefactor
.
 And thus when I have departed this life in hope of eternal life, may I attain unto everlasting rest, where the sound of them that keep festival is unceasing and the delight is endless of them that behold the ineffable beauty of Thy countenance. For Thou 
art the true desire and the unutterable gladness of those who love Thee, O Christ our God, and all creation doth hymn Thee unto the ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6 Of St. Basil the Great, 2: 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32 O Master Christ our God, King of the ages and Creator of all things, I thank Thee fo
r all the good things Thou hast bestowed upon me and for the communion of Thy most pure and life-giving Mysteries. I pray Thee, therefore, O Good One and Lover of mankind: Keep me under Thy protection and in the shadow of Thy wings and grant me, even unto
 
my last breath, to partake worthily, with a pure conscience, of Thy holy Things unto the remission of sins and life eternal. For Thou art the Bread of Life, the Source of Holiness, the Giver of good things, and unto Thee do we send up glory, together with
 the Father and the Holy Spirit, now and ever, and to the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6 Verses of Metaphrastes, 3: 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32 O Thou Who givest me willingly Thy Flesh as food, \line Thou Who art fire, that doth consume the unworthy, 
\line Burn me not, O my Creator, \line But rather enter Thou into my members,\line Into all my joints, my reigns, my heart. \line Burn up the thorns of all my sins. \line Purify my soul, sanctify my thoughts. \line 
Strengthen my substance together with my bones. \line Enlighten the my simple five senses. \line Nail down the whole of me with Thy fear. \line Ever protect, preserve, and keep me \line From every soul-corrupting deed and word. \line 
Purify and cleanse and adorn me; \line Make me comely, give me understanding and enlighten me. \line Make me the dwelling-place of Thy Spirit alone, \line And no longer a habitation of sin, \line That from me as Thine abode through the entry of Communion 
\line Every evildoer, every passion may flee from me as from fire. \line As intercessors I offer unto Thee all the saints,\line The Commanders of the Bodiless Hosts, \line Thy Forerunner, the wise Apostles, \line And Thine undefiled pure Mother, \line 
Whose entreaties do Thou accept, O my compassionate Christ. \line And make Thy servant a child of light. \line For Thou alone art our sanctification, O Good One, \line And the radiance of our souls, \line And to Thee as our God and Master,\line W
e all send up glory as is meet, every day. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6 Another Prayer: 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32 
O Lord Jesus Christ our God, may Thy Holy Body, be unto me for life eternal, and Thy Precious Blood for the remission of sins; And may this Eucharist be to me for joy, health, and gladness. And a
t Thy dread Second Coming, vouchsafe me, a sinner, to stand at the right hand of Thy glory, through the intercessions of Thy most pure Mother and of all Thy Saints. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6 Another Prayer, To the Most Holy Theotokos: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32 All-holy Lady, Theotokos, light of my darkene
d soul, my hope, protection, refuge, consolation, my joy; I thank thee that thou hast vouchsafed me, who am unworthy, to be a partaker of the most pure Body and precious Blood of thy Son. O thou who gavest birth to the true Light, do thou enlighten the sp
i
ritual eyes of my heart; thou who didst gavest birth to the Source of Immortality, revive me who am dead in sin; thou who art the loving-compassionately Mother of the merciful God, have mercy on me and grant me compunction and contrition in my heart, and 
h
umility in my thoughts, and the recall of my thoughts from their captivity. And vouchsafe me until my last breath to receive without condemnation the sanctification of the most Pure Mysteries for the healing of soul and body; And grant me tears of repenta
nce and confession, with which to hymn and glorify thee all the days of my life; For blessed and glorified art Thou unto the ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs20\cf6 Then: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32 
Now lettest Thou Thy servant depart in peace, O Master, according to Thy word: for mine eyes have seen Thy salvation, which Thou hast prepared before the face of all peoples; a light of revelation for the Gentiles, and the glory of Thy people Israel. 

\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32 Holy God, Holy Mighty, Holy Immortal : have mercy on us }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Thrice.}{\fs32  
\par Glory be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit: now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32 All-holy Trinity, have mercy on us. Lord, cleanse us from our sins. Master, Pardon our iniquities. Holy God, visit and heal our infirmities for thy Name's sake. 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32 Lord, have mercy }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Thrice.}{\fs32  
\par Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit: now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32 Our Father, who art in the heavens, hallowed be thy Name; thy kingdom come; thy will be done on earth, as it is in heaven. Give us this day our daily bread; and f
orgive us our debts, as we forgive our debtors; and lead us not into temptation. but deliver us from the Evil One. 
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  For thine is the kingdom, and the power, and the glory, of the Father, and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit: now and ever, and unto ages of ages. Amen. 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 \sect }\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl \pard\plain 
\s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Troparion to St John Chrysostom, Eighth Tone:}{\fs32  
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Reader:}{\fs32 
 Grace shining forth from thy mouth like a beacon hath illumined the universe, and disclosed to the world treasures of uncovetousness, and shown us the heights of humility; but 
while instructing us by Thy words, O Father John Chrysostom, intercede with the Word, Christ our God, to save our souls.
\par  Glory... 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Kontakion, 6th Tone: 
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32 From the heavens hast thou received grace, and by thy lips thou dost teach all to worship the One God 
in Trinity, O John Chrysostom, all blessed righteous one. Rightly do we acclaim thee, for thou art a teacher revealing things divine. 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32 Both now... 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs32 O protection of Christians that cannot be put to shame, O Mediation unto the Creator unfailing: Disdain not 
the suppliant voices of sinners; but be thou quick, O good one, to help us who in faith cry unto Thee; hasten to intercession and speed thou to make supplication, thou who dost ever protect, O Theotokos, them that honor thee. 
\par Lord, have mercy }{\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 12 Times}{\fs32  
\par }{\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Most Holy Theotokos save us! 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Reader: }{\fs32 
More honorable than the Cherubim, and beyond compare more glorious than the Seraphim, thee who without defilement gavest birth to God the Word, the very Theotokos, thee do we magnify. 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 Glory to Thee, O Christ, our God and our hope, glory to Thee.}{\fs32  
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Reader: }{\fs32 Glory... Both now.. Lord have mercy Thrice Father bless! 
\par }\pard \qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Priest:}{\fs32  }{\cs47\b\fs36 
May Christ our true God (Who rose from the dead), through the intercessions of His most pure Mother; and of all the Saints, have mercy upon us and save us, for He is good and the Lover of mankind. 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\cs43\b\i\f1\fs28 Reader:}{\fs32  Amen. 
\par }\pard\plain \s25\ql \li360\ri360\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin360\lin360\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs44\i\f1\fs28\cf6 Then, those who have received the Divine Mysteries approach to kiss the Cross 

\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs20\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof 
